The paper deals with a geometric transportation problem, which involves finding a map between two point sets in $\mathbb{R}^d$ with a given demand function. This problem is inherently geometric and involves distance functions such as the $L_p$ metric. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. 

The paper also presents randomized and approximation algorithms, which are common topics in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). 

The paper involves optimization and minimizing a cost function, which falls under cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.IT (Information Theory). 

Overall, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.IT, and cs.LG.
